headline: Exclusive: Elizabeth Warren Warns Banks Against Lending $20 Billion to Argentina
summary: Sen. Elizabeth Warren (D., Mass.) told the biggest banks in the country not to finance a $20 billion loan to Argentina, citing the financial risk the facility would pose both to depositors and U.S. taxpayers.  Warren sent letters to JPMorgan Chase, Bank of America, Citigroup and Goldman Sachs saying that a $20 billion loan to President Javier Milei’s government “would raise serious safety and soundness concerns…given the shaky creditworthiness of Argentina and its apparent lack of valuable collateral.”  The banks have been seeking details from the Treasury Department on how they can be sure they will get their funds back, The Wall Street Journal reported.

headline: Hedge funds boost AI tech bets to highest since 2016, Goldman Sachs says
summary: LONDON (Reuters) -Hedge funds' exposure to artificial intelligence-related tech hardware reached its highest in October since Goldman Sachs started tracking the data in 2016, the U.S. bank said in a client note.  Hedge fund buying in semiconductor and related chip industry stocks, considered to be sensitive to economic and business cycles, suggests speculators believe rising markets have further to go, Goldman said in the note on Thursday, seen by Reuters on Friday.  Hedge fund stock buying centred on long positions, betting these equities would rise, in Asia and U.S. companies, said Goldman.
